All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ByteArrayBuilder
    A utility class that is designed to build an array of bytes.
    ByteArrayTag
    A tag that is designed to hold an array of bytes and may have a name associated with it.
    ByteTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single byte and a name that may be associated with it.
    Chunk
    Class that contains the raw and processed chunk data.
    ChunkLocation
    Class that holds information about the location of a chunk.
    ChunkLocationTable
    Class that holds all the instances of the ChunkLocation class.
    ChunkTimestamp
    Class that contains information about when a chunk was last modified.
    ChunkTimestampTable
    Class the contains the timestamps of all chunks.
    CompoundTag
    A tag that contains an unspecified number of tags that are guaranteed to contain a name and a payload corresponding to the type of that tag.
    DATFile
    An DATFile contains all the methods that can be used to navigate all the data related to a .dat file.
    DATReader
    An DATReader handles all the byte reading operations and is able to construct an instance of a DATFile object from that data.
    DoubleTag
    A tag is designed to hold a single double and a name that may be associated with it.
    EndTag
    A tag that is designed to signal the end of a compound tag.
    FloatTag
    A tag is designed to hold a single float and a name that may be associated with it.
    IntArrayTag
    A tag that is designed to hold an array of ints and may have a name associated with it.
    IntTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single int and a name that may be associated with it.
    ListTag<T extends Tag>
    A tag is designed to a hold a fixed number of tag payloads with a specific tag type.
    LongArrayTag
    A tag that is designed to hold an array of longs and may have a name associated with it.
    LongTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single long and a name that may be associated with it.
    Main  
    MCAFile
    An MCAFile contains all the methods that can be used to navigate all the data related to a .mca file.
    MCAFilePrinter
    Class that prints or returns a string of specific parts of a .mca file.
    MCAReader
    An MCAReader handles all the byte reading operations and is able to construct an instance of a MCAFile object from that data.
    NBTFileInputStream
    A file input stream class that can be used to read and convert bytes to tags according to the specified protocols given by the NBT format.
    RawChunkData
    Class that contains the raw chunk data.
    RawChunkDataReader
    An RawChunkDataReader handles all the byte reading operations and is able to construct an instance of a RawChunkData object from that data.
    ShortTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single short and a name that may be associated with it.
    StringTag
    A tag that is designed to hold a single string and a name that may be associated with it.
    Tag<T>
    An abstract class that outlines the basic fields and methods that all tags must contain.
    TagIterator
    An iterator that is designed to loop through the contained tags within compound and list tags.
    TagOperation
    Functional interface that defines a operation that is used to search for tags that fit certain conditions.
    TagString
    A utility class that designed to stringify an instance of a Tag object in a human readable format.
